<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-33-0716 </DOCNO><TEXT>An overview of the Italian natural gas system and of its foreseen developmentis presented. The policies of the 1981 PEN (National Energy Plan), asfar as natural gas is concerned, are summarized; internal productionand gas imports are briefly discussed. Following the analysis of thepresent uses of natural gas, there is an evaluation of the most promisingareas of development: the problems of matching the temporal diagramsof demand and supply are considered, including gas use in thermoelectricplants. Some consideration is devoted to the organization of gas distributionin the civil sector and, finally, gas prices and tariff structure areanalyzed.</TEXT></DOC>